free-swimming sperm decreased to 10%, and that of sperm bound to immobilized 
laminin decreased to about 50%, whereas viability of sperm bound to immobilized 
suLeA was highest throughout the incubation and 60% at 96 h. These results 
indicate that bovine sperm binding to oviduct suLeA retains sperm for reservoir 
formation and extends sperm lifespan.

