related to life expectancy. In women, smoking and antihypertensive drug use 
emerged as significant factors.Conclusions　Analysis using NDB Open Data showed 
that lifestyle factors such as smoking and drinking, and cardiovascular risk 
factors such as high blood pressure and hyperglycemia, were strongly related to 
life expectancy. These result suggest that it is necessary to focus on the above 
factors when prefectural authorities implement health promotion measures.

